The paper discusses a learning framework based on neural networks to mimic humanoid robot movements, which falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of deep neural networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of graphical tools, which could indicate a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the application of the framework in the RoboCup 3D Soccer Simulation domain suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
